longBusinessSummary: Chuetsu Pulp & Paper Co., Ltd. produces, processes, and sells paper, pulp, and related by-products in Japan and internationally. It operates through two segments: Paper and Pulp Manufacturing Business and Power Generation Business segments. The company offers printing, information, wrapping, processing, base, specialty, and bamboo papers, as well as newspapers and paper bags, paper tubes, cardboards, and paperboards. The company is also involved in the forestry, lumbering, and timber processing activities; manufacture, processing, and trading of chemicals; selling, management, brokerage, and rental of real estate properties; management of sports facilities; and mining, warehousing, and transportation activities, as well as electricity supply activities. In addition, the company engages in the trading and greening business construction; supply of raw materials; designs mechanical equipment; paper cutting, sorting, and packaging products; manufactures and sells cellulose and nanofiber related products, wood chips, pulp, and Mapuka related products; construction repair; insurance agency; and afforestation and greening businesses. Chuetsu Pulp & Paper Co., Ltd. was incorporated in 1947 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.
